   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AAR Healthcare</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AAR Healthcare has its headquarters in Nairobi and operates twenty four clinics in Kenya, Uganda and Tanzania. Through the proposed project AAR will i) open twelve additional clinics and ii) acquire and/or construct up to three hospitals.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">i) Access to healthcare - the project will expand access to quality inpatient and outpatient healthcare  ii) Demonstration effect - the African health sector is fragmented which results in inconsistent quality and higher costs. The Company will act as a consolidator in the sector and if succesful will attract other investors to employ similar strategies, thereby improving quality and reducing healthcare costs. iii) Job creation - the project will create jobs at the new facilities. iv) South-South investment - Kenya has the most advanced private health sector in East Africa. The Company has transferred skills and capital from Kenya into neighbouring Uganda and Tanzania and the proposed expansion will enable the Company to continue and expand upon this transfer.</narrative>
  </description>
